narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take the class! Laguna brings a great energy to the class and makes it fun. The subject matter is cool and you get to read books you would never read in English/Lit classes.

The Latino/a Novel is a great course. Reading intensive--about 1 novel a week and 1 reading response. It exposes its students to many new genres of literature and the books are very informative and often entertaining. I would definitely recommend this course to another student.

You get to read a lot of the best and widely known Latina/o novels as well as reading some others that you may not have heard of. Since it is a seminar, you really get the opportunity to discuss a lot with your classmates. One reading response per week, one presentation, and two papers - this class isn't very demanding with its work, but there is a lot of reading. The list of books are absolutely great, however, so it's definitely worth it.
Great class!! Take it. Take anything with Professor Laguna!

I would recommend this class for anyone who is interested in reading a variety of novels written by Latino authors. This is a great class for anyone who is interested in discussing different facets of latinidad and how these books and authors interact with the western cannon.
